{"title":"Saturday Rad Bazaar Finds","link":"https://theradavist.com/saturday-rad-bazaar-finds-8/","date":1716044713000,"content":"<p><em>Today, we’ve got a fine selection of used goods from the <a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rad Bazaar</a>, our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/the-radavist-group-ride-subscription-plan-and-rad-bazaar/\" target=\"_blank\">Group Ride subscribers</a>‘ selling platform, featuring some unique offerings. Let’s check it all out!</em><span></span><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dc739efc-5cfb-4eae-88ed-e908d64b.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dc739efc-5cfb-4eae-88ed-e908d64b.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dc739efc-5cfb-4eae-88ed-e908d64b.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dc739efc-5cfb-4eae-88ed-e908d64b.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dc739efc-5cfb-4eae-88ed-e908d64b.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/6Q4e0KmX9acmRulAnNA4?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">44 Bikes Marauder</a> $3700</strong></p>\n<p>Custom hardtail mountain bike. Hand built by Kristofer Henry of 44 Bikes in New Hampshire. I am about 6′-2″ and 190 lbs; this bike was custom sized for me, but if you are close in size it will fit. Steel frame with radiused seat tube, internal cable routing for dropper post.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/560252e4-46b9-4dd2-8331-d446f8a4.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/560252e4-46b9-4dd2-8331-d446f8a4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/560252e4-46b9-4dd2-8331-d446f8a4.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/560252e4-46b9-4dd2-8331-d446f8a4.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/560252e4-46b9-4dd2-8331-d446f8a4.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/66hlvqlp26qNW8blWf36?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Merlin Mendocino Frameset</a> $2400</strong></p>\n<p>Beautiful Merlin Titanium Mendocino frameset with seatpost, Chris King headset. Used a couple times on paved paths. My back and neck are jacked so riding is limited according to pain threshold. It’s a beautiful frameset with Merlin quality. Size Medium, comparable to a Salsa Fargo in size. I’m 5’10” and the frame size is perfect for my height.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1332\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/bb1a43eb-c533-42d0-b125-0832d126.jpg?fit=1200,1332&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/bb1a43eb-c533-42d0-b125-0832d126.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/bb1a43eb-c533-42d0-b125-0832d126.jpg?resize=1200,799&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/bb1a43eb-c533-42d0-b125-0832d126.jpg?resize=768,511&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/bb1a43eb-c533-42d0-b125-0832d126.jpg?resize=1536,1023&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/bP1AzzJA1E0FGqM0afQk?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Spectrum / Tom Kellogg 30th Anniversary Eroica Style Road Bike</a> $2500</strong></p>\n<p>This bike offered for sale is approximately equivalent to a 57 road bike from the early 1980s. Note that riders preferred shorter seat posts in that era. Bike would work best for someone 5′ 9″ to 6′, depending on leg and arm length.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dfad27fa-07a5-49e5-9ec5-c4505d43.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dfad27fa-07a5-49e5-9ec5-c4505d43.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dfad27fa-07a5-49e5-9ec5-c4505d43.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dfad27fa-07a5-49e5-9ec5-c4505d43.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/dfad27fa-07a5-49e5-9ec5-c4505d43.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/5rZABE4BKk9dQQnX1yud?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Chumba Del Amo – 58cm Steel Road Bike</a> $4200</strong></p>\n<p>Only ridden outside a few times – it’s a solid ride. Does everything a nice, modern steel frame is expected to. It easily clears 32mm tires, and is probably one of the nicest production frames out there. There are some small wear marks, but nothing terribly distracting.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/5cbde86a-691b-48d7-920e-6f7232bf.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/5cbde86a-691b-48d7-920e-6f7232bf.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/5cbde86a-691b-48d7-920e-6f7232bf.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/5cbde86a-691b-48d7-920e-6f7232bf.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/5cbde86a-691b-48d7-920e-6f7232bf.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/sxIvjmWOndHHi2JcoiDV?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Rodeo Labs Flaanimal 4 54cm w/ 13spd Ekar + SRAM Force</a> $2200</strong></p>\n<p>Selling my trusty and beloved Rodeo Labs Flaanimal 4.0. Whittling the herd as I have acquired a new bike, and no longer adhere ot the N+1 rule. This was the from first publicly available batch in 2017. I’ve raced it in a criterium (overbiked), I’ve done quite a few centuries with it, gone bikepacking with it, it is the most versatile bike I have ever owned. It’s been through a lot (see top tube), but well taken care of.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/99368cd0-7eed-4151-be01-557a3875.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/99368cd0-7eed-4151-be01-557a3875.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/99368cd0-7eed-4151-be01-557a3875.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/99368cd0-7eed-4151-be01-557a3875.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/99368cd0-7eed-4151-be01-557a3875.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/Jx8ftHgLf6fDD5slbSeN?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">2006 Rivendell Rambouillet 58cm</a> $1900</strong></p>\n<p>2006 Rivendell Rambouillet, New bars / bar tape, New stem, New tires, and Recent tune up</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/471e6f0c-12b1-4cfc-97d6-d7291524.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/471e6f0c-12b1-4cfc-97d6-d7291524.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/471e6f0c-12b1-4cfc-97d6-d7291524.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/471e6f0c-12b1-4cfc-97d6-d7291524.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/471e6f0c-12b1-4cfc-97d6-d7291524.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/QA1Rlbkh74Ck8xu3jdpP?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Surly Karate Monkey – Large, 2017</a> $1250</strong></p>\n<p>Do I have to give this thing away???<br />\nWhat began as a stock 2017 Karate Monkey slowly became what you see here.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/2bae826e-96b9-4a88-b1bf-9d79d216.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/2bae826e-96b9-4a88-b1bf-9d79d216.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/2bae826e-96b9-4a88-b1bf-9d79d216.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/2bae826e-96b9-4a88-b1bf-9d79d216.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/2bae826e-96b9-4a88-b1bf-9d79d216.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://radbazaar.theradavist.com/listing/VlW0ZEHboYwvoDGYdBpQ?category=undefined&amp;subcategory=undefined\" target=\"_blank\">1991 Bridgestone MB2 18″</a> $347</strong></p>\n<p>Vintage MTB with the original stock components. Great lugged frame. Rear triangle has been painted to deal with chainsuck scars. Ritchey Logic Prestige main triangle, chromoly rear triangle with ovalized chainstays. Not crimped.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>If you’d like access to a seller’s account on the Rad Bazaar, simply sign up for our Group Ride subscription plan ($6.66 a month or $69.69 a year.) In doing so, you support our independent Reportage, gain access to discounts to our merchandise, and more! See all the details at our <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/the-radavist-group-ride-subscription-plan-and-rad-bazaar/\" target=\"_blank\">Group Ride page</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/saturday-rad-bazaar-finds-8/\">Saturday Rad Bazaar Finds</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"98b1f2a23c9d30db9ead0c19bfd3b36e681efdea25d65bfad1e60a3e6cb8a883","category":"Cycling"}